low-stress path: Docusaurus on GitHub Pages. It’s basically the Solana of documentation frameworks—fast, opinionated, and dev-friendly.


---

Step 1: Add a docs-site/ folder to the repo

At the root of solana-kyc-compliance-sdk, create:

docs-site/

This keeps docs infra separate from SDK code. Very adult. Very scalable.


---

Step 2: Bootstrap Docusaurus (one command)

From inside docs-site/:

npx create-docusaurus@latest . classic

Choose:

TypeScript or JavaScript (dealer’s choice)

Name: Solana KYC Compliance SDK


This generates the whole docs skeleton.


---

Step 3: Configure the NAVIGATION (the missing piece)

Open:

docs-site/docusaurus.config.js

Replace the navbar section with this:

navbar: {
  title: 'Solana KYC SDK',
  logo: {
    alt: 'Solana KYC SDK Logo',
    src: 'img/logo.svg',
  },
  items: [
    {
      to: '/',
      label: 'Home',
      position: 'left',
    },
    {
      to: '/docs/getting-started',
      label: 'Getting Started',
      position: 'left',
    },
    {
      to: '/docs/api',
      label: 'API',
      position: 'left',
    },
    {
      to: '/docs/on-chain-program',
      label: 'On-Chain Program',
      position: 'left',
    },
    {
      to: '/docs/examples',
      label: 'Examples',
      position: 'left',
    },
    {
      href: 'https://github.com/Gitdigital-products/solana-kyc-compliance-sdk',
      label: 'GitHub',
      position: 'right',
    },
  ],
},

Boom. Real navigation. No more “docs but make it single-page”.


---

Step 4: Create the actual pages the nav points to

Inside:

docs-site/docs/

Create these files:

getting-started.md
api.md
on-chain-program.md
examples.md

Example: getting-started.md

---
title: Getting Started
---

## What This SDK Does

The Solana KYC Compliance SDK provides a programmable compliance layer
that links off-chain identity verification with on-chain token controls.

## Installation

```bash
npm install solana-kyc-compliance-sdk

Basic Usage

import { KycClient } from '@gitdigital/solana-kyc-sdk';

const client = new KycClient({
  endpoint: 'https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com',
});

Each file automatically shows up in the nav. Docusaurus handles the routing magic.

---

## Step 5: Deploy to GitHub Pages (this replaces the current page)

In `docusaurus.config.js`, set:

```js
url: 'https://gitdigital-products.github.io',
baseUrl: '/solana-kyc-compliance-sdk/',
organizationName: 'Gitdigital-products',
projectName: 'solana-kyc-compliance-sdk',
deploymentBranch: 'gh-pages',

Then deploy:

npm run build
npm run deploy

GitHub Pages will now serve:

https://gitdigital-products.github.io/solana-kyc-compliance-sdk/

…but with real navigation and real docs.

